11. Cookie Policy
This Cookie Policy applies to Cookies and other technologies that are similar in function on the Company's website. The purpose of this policy is to inform you about Cookies used by the Company, the Cookies’ tasks and how to manage your Cookies.
The Company's website uses Cookies to provide your experience in using website and help the Company improve the efficiency of the website. Cookies do not pose any threat to your device, and the content within Cookies are called out or readable only on the website that created said Cookies..
1.    Types of Cookies Used by the Company and Cookie Duration
The Company uses four types of Cookies namely:
•    Strictly Necessary Cookies
•    Analytical/Performance Cookies
•    Functionality Cookies
•    Targeting Cookies
These Cookies serve different purposes as explained below:The Company uses first-party and third-party Cookies. First-party Cookies are Cookies files created and recorded by the websites you visit. This type of Cookies is readable on the creator’s website and only records your data. Third-party Cookies are cookie files created and recorded by domains other than the websites you visit and can freely share Cookies files that recorded your data to any other websites.
2.    Additionally, the Cookies used by the Company are session Cookies and persistent Cookies. Session Cookies are temporary Cookies that remain in your device until you leave the Company’s website. Persistent Cookies remain in your device even after you leave the Company’s website or until you personally delete them. (How long the cookies remain in your device depends on the duration or “age” of the Cookies and your browser settings.)
Consent Strictly Necessary Cookies are always enabled on your device based on the Company's legitimate interests in ensuring security in using the Company’s website. However, the Company shall request your consent if other types of Cookies are used.. If you wish to change your Cookie settings or withdraw consent for the processing of Personal Data from Cookies, you can learn more in the Cookie Settings section.
3.    Using Cookies
The Company uses cookies when you visit the Company’s website The Cookies are categorized by their functions as follow:
•    Strictly Necessary Cookies: This type of Cookies is essential for the function of the website. This includes cookies that allows you to access data and features on the Company’s website securely.
•    Analytical/Performance Cookies: This type of Cookies collects your website usage data so that the Company can analyze, evaluate, improve and/or develop product/service contents and website of the Company in order to improve your experience in using the website in addition to collecting statistical data related to usage methods and website visit behaviors which can help improve the functions of the website to allow users to easily search for what they want.
•    Functionality Cookies: This type of Cookies is used to remember you when you revisit the Company’s website which can help the Company to present content and meet your needs as well as remember your site preferences, such as language, region or font, more easily and quickly so that you don’t have to provide the data or settings every time you visit the website.
•    Targeting Cookies: This type of Cookies records your website visit history, web pages you visit and links you visit, which may include the Personal Data you use to create a profile, so that the Company can analyze and present content, products and/or services and/or advertisements that may interest you.
•    Third-Party Cookies: The Company’s website or application may contain links to third-party websites or application. You should study the cookie policies and privacy policies of the third-party websites, which may differ from the Company’s website, on the respective third-party websites in order to understand the methods used by the third party to collect your data for use. In any case, the Company is not responsible for any contents, policies, damages or actions that result from any third-party website or application.
4.    Cookie Settings
You can disable cookies by adjusting your browser settings on your device. Here are instructions for popular browsers:
•    Chrome: Cookies Setting in Chrome
•    Firefox: Cookies Setting in Firefox
•    Safari: Cookies Setting in Safari
•    Internet Explorer: Cookies Setting in Internet Explorer
Disabling cookies may affect your ability to efficiently access and use the Company's website. For more information, please visit www.aboutcookies.org.
12.เจ้าหน้าที่คุ้มครองข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล
บริษัทได้แต่งตั้งเจ้าหน้าที่คุ้มครองข้อมูลส่วนบุคคลเพื่อตรวจสอบการดำเนินการที่เกี่ยวกับการเก็บ รวบรวม ใช้ หรือ เปิดเผยข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล ให้สอดคล้องตามพ.ร.บ. คุ้มครองข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล และ นโยบาย ระเบียบ ประกาศ คำสั่ง ของบริษัท รวมทั้งประสานงานและให้ความร่วมมือกับสำนักงานคณะกรรมการคุ้มครองข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล และมีหน้าที่อื่น ๆ ตามที่พ.ร.บ. คุ้มครองข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล
12.    Data Protection Officer
The Company has appointed a Data Protection Officer to oversee compliance with the PDPA and Company’s policies, regulations, announcements, and orders. The Data Protection Officer also coordinates and cooperates with the Office of the Personal Data Protection Commission and performs other duties as stipulated by the PDPA.
13.คำถามที่เกี่ยวกับนโยบายความเป็นส่วนตัว
หากท่านมีข้อเสนอแนะ หรือต้องการสอบถามข้อมูลเกี่ยวกับรายละเอียดการเก็บรวบรวม ใช้ และเปิดเผยข้อมูลส่วนบุคคลของท่าน รวมถึงการขอใช้สิทธิตามนโยบายฉบับนี้ ท่านสามารถติดต่อบริษัท และ/หรือเจ้าหน้าที่คุ้มครองข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล ผ่านช่องทางดังนี้
ติดต่อได้ที่ เจ้าหน้าที่คุ้มครองข้อมูลส่วนบุคคล (Data Protection Officer)  e-mail : dpo@majorcineplex.com
13.    Questions Regarding Privacy Policy
If you have suggestions or inquiries regarding the details of how your Personal Data is collected, used, and disclosed, including requests to exercise rights under this Policy, you can contact the Company and/or the Data Protection Officer through the following channels:
Contact: Data Protection Officer (DPO) Email: dpo@majorcineplex.com
